4. POLYNOMIAL LIE ENCODING
======================================================================

  Tournament poly = (z-2)(z-3)
    Roots: KEY1, KEY2
    Coefficients: [1, -5, 6]
    Lie encoding: ['1', '-(KEY1+KEY2)', 'h(G2)']

  Petersen min poly = (z-3)(z-1)(z+2)
    Roots: KEY2, 1, -KEY1
    Coefficients: [1, -2, -5, 6]
    Lie encoding: ['1', '-KEY1', '-(KEY1+KEY2)', 'h(G2)']

  (z-3)(z^2-5z+6) = (z-2)(z-3)^2
    Roots: KEY1, KEY2, KEY2
    Coefficients: [1, -8, 21, -18]
    Lie encoding: ['1', '-rank(E8)', 'H_forb_2', '-h(E7)']

  (z+2)(z^2-5z+6) = (z+2)(z-2)(z-3)
    Roots: -KEY1, KEY1, KEY2
    Coefficients: [1, -3, -4, 12]
    Lie encoding: ['1', '-KEY2', '-rank(F4)', 'h(F4)']

